HEADWORD: Circean
<hw>Cir*ce"an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Circaeus</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having the characteristics of Circe,
daughter of Sol and Perseis, a mythological enchantress, who first
charmed her victims and then changed them to the forms of beasts;
pleasing, but noxious; <as>as, a <ex>Circean</ex>
draught</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

